<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Merge and Destroy (Posts about tipps&amp;tricks)</title><link>https://encarsia.github.io/</link><description></description><atom:link href="https://encarsia.github.io/en/categories/cat_tippstricks.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 15 Sep 2018 07:50:25 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>New widgets in old Glade files</title><link>https://encarsia.github.io/en/posts/neue-widgets-in-alten-glade-dateien/</link><dc:creator>Anke (encarsia)</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Problem: disabled widgets in older Glade files&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It may occur that certain widgets in Glade are greyed out after opened in Glade.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;a class="reference external image-reference" href="https://encarsia.github.io/images/glade_widgetsinactive.png"&gt;&lt;img alt="/images/glade_widgetsinactive.thumbnail.png" src="https://encarsia.github.io/images/glade_widgetsinactive.thumbnail.png"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A hint is hown in tooltips like&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;a class="reference external image-reference" href="https://encarsia.github.io/images/glade_widgetsinactive_tooltip.png"&gt;&lt;img alt="/images/glade_widgetsinactive_tooltip.thumbnail.png" src="https://encarsia.github.io/images/glade_widgetsinactive_tooltip.thumbnail.png"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cause for this behaviour is the Gtk+ version given at the beginning of the file:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code xml"&gt;&lt;a name="rest_code_9701f40f4bc441fdafaa62927c678dd9-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="cp"&gt;&amp;lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_9701f40f4bc441fdafaa62927c678dd9-2"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;&amp;lt;!-- Generated with glade 3.20.1 --&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_9701f40f4bc441fdafaa62927c678dd9-3"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;lt;interface&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_9701f40f4bc441fdafaa62927c678dd9-4"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;lt;requires&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="na"&gt;lib=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;"gtk+"&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="na"&gt;version=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;"3.0"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;/&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_9701f40f4bc441fdafaa62927c678dd9-5"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;  ...
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;This line will not be altered even if the file is saved by a more recent Glade version.
So you just manually replace &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;"3.0"&lt;/tt&gt; by a current version (&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;"3.20"&lt;/tt&gt; at present).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>glade</category><guid>https://encarsia.github.io/en/posts/neue-widgets-in-alten-glade-dateien/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 25 Oct 2017 08:12:09 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>